com.timesten.jdbc.connectionpool
Class TimesTenPooledStatement

java.lang.Object
  com.timesten.jdbc.connectionpool.TimesTenPooledStatement
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.timesten.jdbc.TimesTenStatement, java.sql.Statement, java.sql.Wrapper
public final class TimesTenPooledStatement
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.timesten.jdbc.TimesTenStatement

Represents a TimesTen statement. This class should not be instantiated directly. Instances of this classs are manipulated via methods in the associated TimesTenPooledConnection and TimesTenConnectionPool classes.

This class implements the standard TimesTenStatement interface, plus some additional methods.

Any methods which are not explicitly documented behave identically to the corresponding method in TimesTenStatement.

Any individual instance of this class should not be shared amongst multiple threads.

If the connection that owns this statement has been invalidated due to a failover most methods will throw a TTCP_ERR_STMT_INVALID exception.

public final java.lang.String getLabel()
Returns the textual label associated with this statement. The label is defined when the statement is created via the the addStatement() method in the TimesTenConnectionPool class.

close

public final void close()
Silently does nothing. A TimesTenPoolPreparedStatement can only be closed by the owning TimesTenPooledConnection object which in turn will only close the statement when directed to by its owning TimestenConnectionPool object, via of the removeStatement() method.
